==English==

===Proper noun===
'''Denise'''
# a female [[given name]], the feminine form of [[Dennis]]  Name used with various spellings in Dutch, English, Greek and French. Its source is Dionysius (Dionysus), a male Greek name meaning "Dedicated to Dionysus". Dionysus is the mythological Greek god of wine responsible for growth of the vines and the originator of winemaking.

